<br>
Well everyone, it's time to move onto the mortality phase of your progression.  As you know, this means that not only will you get to experience growth and greater joy but will also be vulnerable to tempation and suffering, but I'll be patient with you and provide a way for you to correct your mistakes.  It's going to be a rough ride but in the end it will be worth it.<br>
<br>
Because you will be behaving like idiots for a good portion of the time and using Me as and excuse for it (OK, &quot;idiots&quot; is my choice of words there, He is much more patient and kind than that) things like prejudice and discrimination are going to make it more difficult to pull this plan off but we'll chip away at it as best we can until everything that is needed is fulfilled.<br>
<br>
In other words, I think God would love nothing more than if everyone would choose to do what is right, but he will not take away our agency.  Therefore, He just has to work with us the best He can.  I don't think it is that he is withholding things from us, I think he tries to give us (meaning humankind as a whole) as much as we can handle, and sometimes that's just a little bit at a time, which explains things like &quot;first tot he Jew, then the gentile&quot; and how the priesthood didn't go to every lineage at once, etc.  People as a whole were not ready for it.  I mean, the LDS church members just about got exterminated as it was, kwim?  This would be consistent with how I believe other things have been done. for instance, early in the LDS church they tried to live something called the &quot;law of consecration&quot; where everything was held in common.  It had to be done voluntarily.  It also would only work if the people were truly unselfish and you know what?  They couldn't do it.  So, God said OK, we won't ask you to go that far yet and provided a &quot;lesser law&quot; to help them grow by in the meantime.<br>
<br>
Just more rambling from me.  And can someone tell me why my house is such a mess? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
