<br>
One man to many women and the higher sex drive of men is in our genes from the time we roamed around in groups like apes, the dominant (and most genetically superior) male mating with all the females, not to outbreed the other groups of animals but to produce the most &quot;fit&quot; offspring. The drive then is not born of male stupidity, rather male sex drive innate and necessary at one time to survive and procreate the species.<br>
<br>
My own view and personal experience of marriage is much broader and richer than that of a contract between two fertile adults to breed as much as possible to bring on the spirit babies and outpopulate the Catholics and other religions, so to me it's always a shame that the xians in our society impose this on others. What of the union between homosexuals, infertile couples and the elderly past breeding age then? <br>
<br>
Also--it's a documented fact, and I went into this more on the birth control thread that the longer a woman waits to get married and have children, the more control over when she gets pregnant and the less children she has the better for her and the children in general. It's better economically, socially, politically and environmentally and I can understand why a guy who thinks my highest purpose is to pop out 6 or 7 spirit  babies gives me less consideration in the workplace. This view of women naturally leads to thinking women don't need as much or any education, equal treatment in the workplace, as much salary etc. <br>
<br>
In this way, to push women (whether directly by scripture or socially to snatch up the first boy returning from mission and marry him before you're out of your teens) to marry so young and have 6 or more children is harmful. Technology, social/political progress and medical advances in birth control have freed us from this but it seems some are still bound by religion and that's too bad, not just for them but for the overpopulated and overwrought planet we live on.<br>
